Text: This week there were things i think the team and I could have done better.
We had our last in-person meeting on Monday where we split some of the final tasks but we didn't really follow up with each other much over the rest of the week.
I think this was a mistake as the presentation and deliverables are where all of our work comes together to make one final product.
We should have spent more time checking in and working collaboratively in this time to avoid some of the overlap we had with our own tasks and to get on the same page with the presentation.
I didn't understand the importance of this until the night before when a few misunderstandings between the team the became apparent.
I think this affected our presentation quality, especially the structure of it but also the content.
Next time i would suggest the team work more collaboratively at the end of the project as not doing so can diminish the value of the work done previously.
Also, for myself i think i could have prepared for the presentation better.

I thought i was familiar enough with the content to where i could just talk about certain points off the cuff, but i felt that once i started talking i was kind of forgetting things that i expected to be able to explain easily.
There were many other things i was planning to include but i forgot at the time because i was thinking too much about what to say.
Next time i will make the actual presenting part of the preparation a bigger focus for myself and have a much clearer schedule for my talking points and delivery of information.
Finally, there was some misunderstanding about the invitation for Rodney to come to the talk.
This was a mistake we made by not discussing it within the team.
I am glad Rodney came as it was good to talk to him in person about the project and it confirmed that he was fairly pleased with what we delivered.
Next time i will try to remember to consider who might have an interest in seeing a presentation i'm involved in so i can check whether its appropriate send them an invite.
